<p>GDP growth: 2.9% GDP: $290bn (PPP: $538bn) Inflation: 11.0% Population: 87.7m GDP per head: $3,300 (PPP: $6,130)</p>

<p>In a year for keeping promises, the army must hand back power, the country must hold elections that are free and fair, the constitutional assembly must draft an inclusive charter, and the new team must get the economy back on an even keel. Economic liberalisation is seen as a discredited legacy of the last regime, and state intervention may rise. Revolution was bad for growth; re-starting the economy will be the top priority in 2012, with the expansion likely to approach 3%.</p>

